263
00:13:10,083 --> 00:13:12,708
a term a concept

264
00:13:13,250 --> 00:13:14,291
a name

265
00:13:15,041 --> 00:13:17,875
no permanent person exists here

266
00:13:18,750 --> 00:13:22,541
this perfectly captures Buddha's teaching on no self

267
00:13:23,625 --> 00:13:26,958
the Visuddhimagga a cornerstone of Buddhist philosophy

268
00:13:27,291 --> 00:13:29,375
presents another compelling perspective

269
00:13:29,375 --> 00:13:31,541
through the metaphor of a lighting lamp

270
00:13:32,125 --> 00:13:34,000
each flame appears continuous

271
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:36,625
yet is never the same from moment to moment

272
00:13:36,958 --> 00:13:40,541
